                        <interp inst="t18370508-name-228" type="surname" value="HUBE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370508-name-228" type="given" value="JOHN NICHOLAS"></interp>JOHN NICHOLAS HUBE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a newsvender. The prisoner had been five or six months in my employ—he was accustomed to receive monies for me, and ought to have accounted the same day—he never delivered this money to me from Stewart.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DOANE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> What was the date of this embez<lb></lb>zlement? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I cannot exactly say—it was in 1836—my quarterly bills go in in June, and it must have been shortly after that—1 have no books here—I never saw him from the time he went out till I took him into custody—he was then in the employ of my aunt, in the same business.</p>
               <p>
